Bestiary: {
	ImportantFlavorText: Important Flavor Text!
	ExamplePerson_1: Hailing from a mysterious greyscale cube world, the Example Person is here to help you understand everything about tModLoader.
	ExamplePerson_2: Built of blocks with arms of steel. Pumps iron day and night.
	ExampleBoneMerchant_1: Hailing from a mysterious greyscale cube world, the Example Bone Merchant will show you how to make a mysterious merchant underground with tModLoader.
	ExampleBoneMerchant_2: Built with bone blocks and arms of steel. Throws bones day and night.
	ExampleTownPet: A blocky Town Pet to bring extra cuteness to the town.
	PartyZombie: This type of zombie for some reason really likes to spread confetti around. Otherwise, it behaves just like a normal zombie.
	MinionBossBody: Example Minion Boss that spawns minions on spawn, summoned with a spawn item. Showcases boss minion handling, multiplayer considerations, and custom boss bar.
	ExampleCritterNPC: The most adorable goodest spicy child. Do not dare be mean to him!
	ExampleZombieThief: This type of zombie really like Example Items. They steal them as soon as they find some.
	MinionBossMinion: A minion protecting his boss from taking damage by sacrificing itself. If none are alive, the boss is exposed to damage.
	ExampleWormHead: Looks like a Digger fell into some aqua-colored paint. Oh well.
}

